      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TAW MAJOR (1) is a super honest type rarely out of the placings, including wins at his last two on end, the latest at this track (29.53). Solid record here including 10 wins. Rates strongly and will go close from the inside draw. DEWANA STAR (2) was safely held in tougher company last start after drifting back at Shepparton, but prior to that won comfortably by 4.5 lengths at Shepparton (24.86) beating Dramatical in a Special conditions H on March 16. Goes very well from this draw with four wins and two minor placings from seven starts. Shapes as one to consider. CANYA HANDLE IT (3) was well off top last time, finishing 4th (30.23) in a Grade 5 at this track. Form here at this distance is strong including three wins. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Has ability and can measure up. SHE'S FEARLESS (7) impressed last start, winning in good time. Right in the mix.",
